org.matsim.api.core.v01.network

Interface Node

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Attributable, BasicLocation<Node>, Identifiable<Node>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    RoutingNetworkNode
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractRoutingNetworkNode, ArrayRoutingNetworkNode, ImaginaryNode, RoutingNetworkImaginaryNode, TransitRouterNetwork.TransitRouterNetworkNode

    public interface Node
extends BasicLocation<Node>, Identifiable<Node>, Attributable
    A topological representation of an network node. This interface deliberately does NOT have a back pointer ... ... since, at this level, one should be able to get the relevant container from the context. (This becomes clear if you think about a nodeId/linkId given by person.)
